        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 2:23PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Forked Deer, or 11 miles east of Ripley, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Halls, Chestnut Bluff, Forked Deer, Unionville, Maury City,
Friendship, Gates, South Fork, Poplar Grove, Hawkinsville, Fowlkes,
Curve, Dog Hill, Bonicord, Double Bridges, Frog Jump, Stokes, Maury
Junction, Toulon, and Tigrett.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
